### Task 5 :  279412f945939ba78ce0758d3fd83daa

Hash Type : MD4

The commands required to crack the hash using both Hashcat and John the Ripper have been provided as part of this exercise. However, for this task, CrackStation ( https://crackstation.net/) was used to demonstrate an alternative hash-cracking approach and to highlight the use of online hash lookup services as an additional attack vector.

- Hash Cat

```purescript
hashcat -m 900 -a 0 hash.txt rockyou.txt
```

- John the Ripper

```purescript
john --format=raw-md4 --wordlist=rockyou.txt hash.txt
```

Since the previous tasks focused extensively on offline password-cracking tools, this exercise was intended to showcase a different methodology that may be leveraged during an assessment. In real-world scenarios, practitioners often utilize both offline and online resources in parallel to improve efficiency and maximize the chances of successful hash recovery.

